    editor = VideoCollabEditor()\n    async with websockets.serve(editor.handler, "localhost", 8765):\n        await asyncio.Future()  # Run forever\n\nif __name__ == "__main__":\n    asyncio.run(main())\n```\n\nThis code sets up a basic WebSocket server that can handle client connections, register and unregister clients, and notify all connected clients of changes to the video data. It also includes a simple handler to process incoming messages and update the video data accordingly.\n\nOnce Agent1 has created this initial framework, they should communicate the results to Agent3 for further revision and optimization.'}, 'task_results': [{'agent1': 'Result from the model:\nResult from the function:{"success": false, "error-msg": "Solution file already exists at C:\\\\Users\\\\70454\\\\Desktop\\\\PredictDesign\\\\results\\\\parallel_api_test\\\\runtime_configs\\\\coding\\\\task_34_workspace\\\\solution.py. Operation aborted."}'}, {'agent2': 'Result from the model:\nResult from the function:{"success": true, "message": "Successfully completed session 76b1e317-5a08-4086-a819-ecb4b6c46ed3", "full_chat_history": "In Session 76b1e317-5a08-4086-a819-ecb4b6c46ed3 \\nFrom agent2 to agent1: Hi Agent1,\\n\\nI haven\'t received the initial code framework for the VideoCollabEditor project yet. Could you please share it so I can review and provide feedback?\\n\\nBest regards,\\nAgent2\\n", "session_id": "### Summary of Chat History: VideoCollabEditor Project\\n\\n**Context and Participants:**\\n- **Agent1**: Responsible for sharing the initial code framework for the VideoCollabEditor project.\\n- **Agent2**: Awaiting the code framework to review and provide feedback.\\n- **Agent3**: Will be involved in optimizing the code after Agent2\'s revisions.\\n\\n**Key Points and Themes:**\\n1. **Initial Code Framework Request:**\\n   - **Agent2** has not received the initial code framework from **Agent1**.\\n   - **Agent2** has requested the code to begin the review and revision process.\\