          if not data:\\n                    break\\n                message = json.loads(data)\\n                self.message_queue.put(message)\\n                self.process_message(message)\\n        finally:\\n            self.remove_client(client_socket)\\n            client_socket.close()\\n\\n    def process_message(self, message):\\n        # Placeholder for message processing logic\\n        print(f\\"Received message: {message}\\")\\n        self.broadcast_message(message)\\n\\n    def start_server(self, host=\'127.0.0.1\', port=65432):\\n        with socket.socket(socket.AF_INET, socket.SOCK_STREAM) as s:\\n            s.bind((host, port))\\n            s.listen()\\n            print(f\\"Server started on {host}:{port}\\")\\n            while True:\\n                client_socket, addr = s.accept()\\n                print(f\\"Connected by {addr}\\")\\n                self.add_client(client_socket)\\n                client_thread = threading.Thread(target=self.handle_client, args=(client_socket,))\\n                client_thread.start()\\n\\nif __name__ == \'__main__\':\\n    editor = VideoCollabEditor()\\n    editor.start_server()"\n}\n```\n\nThis skeleton sets up a basic server-client architecture for the VideoCollabEditor system. It includes methods for adding and removing clients, broadcasting messages, handling client connections, and processing messages. The `start_server` method initializes the server and listens for incoming connections.\n\nPlease ensure that the `solution.py` file is either cleared or a new location is specified to avoid conflicts, and then proceed with the development process as outlined.', 'continue_simulation': True, 'communications': ["In Session 76b1e317-5a08-4086-a819-ecb4b6c46ed3 \nFrom agent2 to agent1: Hi Agent1,\n\nI haven't received the initial code framework for the VideoCollabEditor project yet. Could you please share it so I can review and provide feedback?\n\nBest regards,\nAgent2\n"], 'total_milestones': 0, 'agent